{
  "text": "We see that bab = b is redundant in Statement (iii). In fact, by using some other equations in (iii), we can check that bab = bapb = pb = b. Also from the definition of a [CITATION_1] p,q , it is easy to check that if a (2) p,q exists, then Statements (ii) and (iii) hold. But we can show by following example that Statement (iii) does not imply Statement (i).",
